1
00:00:08,499 --> 00:00:12,545
‐ [roars]

2
00:00:19,719 --> 00:00:21,178
‐ Elysium.

3
00:00:21,178 --> 00:00:24,181
<i>["Gravitation" by Angela]</i>

4
00:00:24,181 --> 00:00:27,309
<i>[woman singing in Japanese]</i>

5
00:00:27,309 --> 00:00:34,316
<i>♪ ♪</i>

6
00:02:25,427 --> 00:02:27,513
‐ It's still alive.

7
00:02:30,224 --> 00:02:32,643
How dare you show yourselves.

8
00:02:38,774 --> 00:02:40,609
Where are you?

9
00:02:40,609 --> 00:02:44,029
‐ See, now we're out.
[laughs]

10
00:02:44,989 --> 00:02:47,575
‐ [panting] Hold on.

11
00:02:47,575 --> 00:02:49,451
Let me rest a minute.

12
00:02:53,038 --> 00:02:55,374
‐ [groans]

13
00:02:55,374 --> 00:02:57,418
‐ You bastards!

14
00:02:58,836 --> 00:03:03,173
‐ The Silver Tribe's ship,
did it escape the void?

15
00:03:03,173 --> 00:03:05,926
‐ The pathway to Elysium
has been discovered.

16
00:03:05,926 --> 00:03:08,220
We'll have to make our way there
in this vessel.

17
00:03:08,220 --> 00:03:10,347
We can recuperate
during the trip.

18
00:03:10,347 --> 00:03:13,392
‐ Damn you! You have all
betrayed our cause!

19
00:03:13,392 --> 00:03:15,853
‐ That isn't true,
Phaetho O.

20
00:03:15,853 --> 00:03:17,187
We have not.

21
00:03:17,187 --> 00:03:18,772
‐ We've done nothing
that violates

22
00:03:18,772 --> 00:03:21,483
the nature of our labors.
You must hear us out.

23
00:03:21,483 --> 00:03:23,193
‐ The majority
of the Silver Tribe

24
00:03:23,193 --> 00:03:24,695
agrees with Prome O.

25
00:03:24,695 --> 00:03:28,198
Discord comes only from those
like you and Rom Ror.

26
00:03:28,198 --> 00:03:29,450
‐ [grunts]

27
00:03:29,450 --> 00:03:31,327
‐ Once Rom realizes
he won't gain

28
00:03:31,327 --> 00:03:35,372
the power of the Golden Tribe,
he'll have Yuty destroy Elysium,

29
00:03:35,372 --> 00:03:38,042
and that is the last
of Yuty's Labors.

30
00:03:38,042 --> 00:03:40,628
It is my sworn duty
to protect the power

31
00:03:40,628 --> 00:03:43,797
that lies on that planet.
That is one of my Labors.

32
00:03:43,797 --> 00:03:45,674
Now go.

33
00:03:45,674 --> 00:03:47,384
MAN: Elysium.

34
00:03:47,384 --> 00:03:51,388
The path has been found.
It would be wise to listen.

35
00:03:51,388 --> 00:03:53,599
LECTY:
Go, not only for your own sake

36
00:03:53,599 --> 00:03:55,184
and the sake
of your own tribe,

37
00:03:55,184 --> 00:03:57,895
but for the benefit
of every tribe in the universe.

38
00:03:57,895 --> 00:04:02,149
But then again, you're welcome
to stay here and challenge us.

39
00:04:11,116 --> 00:04:14,411
‐ Rom Ror and his Nodos
will destroy

40
00:04:14,411 --> 00:04:16,914
each and every one of you.

41
00:04:18,540 --> 00:04:21,794
‐ May the stars guide them
on their way.

42
00:04:24,588 --> 00:04:25,923
‐ Elysium.

43
00:04:25,923 --> 00:04:28,342
It is nothing but a dream,

44
00:04:28,342 --> 00:04:30,386
an illusion from long ago.

45
00:04:30,386 --> 00:04:32,429
The Golden Tribe
didn't leave a thing

46
00:04:32,429 --> 00:04:34,431
for the new masters
of the universe.

47
00:04:34,431 --> 00:04:38,560
If they wish to leave nothing
behind, I shall assist them,

48
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:42,773
by destroying every last trace
of their existence.

49
00:04:42,773 --> 00:04:44,650
‐ Erase me.

50
00:04:44,650 --> 00:04:46,735
Please.

51
00:04:46,735 --> 00:04:50,572
You have to erase me,
Kervius.

52
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:05,796
‐ We're getting closer.
I can feel it.

53
00:05:05,796 --> 00:05:07,464
‐ Bee, report.

54
00:05:07,464 --> 00:05:08,966
BEE NO BEE:
The repairs are expected to take

55
00:05:08,966 --> 00:05:10,592
at least 80 hours, master.

56
00:05:10,592 --> 00:05:13,929
‐ Will it be possible to jump
before the repairs are done?

57
00:05:13,929 --> 00:05:15,472
‐ No, I'm afraid not.

58
00:05:15,472 --> 00:05:17,725
‐ There is a cease fire
with the Silver Tribe,

59
00:05:17,725 --> 00:05:20,477
but factions within the group
remain a threat.

60
00:05:20,477 --> 00:05:23,063
Our main focus is still
to reach the coordinates

61
00:05:23,063 --> 00:05:24,523
indicated by the princess.

62
00:05:24,523 --> 00:05:26,608
‐ I'm detecting
a large magnetic storm.

63
00:05:26,608 --> 00:05:29,862
It's position will interfere
with the ship's current course.

64
00:05:29,862 --> 00:05:32,239
‐ And there's
no alternate route, huh?

65
00:05:32,239 --> 00:05:34,408
Well, it's nothing
the "Argonaut" can't handle.

66
00:05:34,408 --> 00:05:38,037
Full speed ahead!
Shields at maximum capacity!

67
00:05:43,792 --> 00:05:45,044
‐ No.

68
00:05:51,717 --> 00:05:53,052
WOMAN: Speed is increasing.

69
00:05:53,052 --> 00:05:55,179
All navigations systems are
losing function.

70
00:05:55,179 --> 00:05:57,848
Celestial locations
completely off‐line.

71
00:05:57,848 --> 00:05:59,600
‐ This is no magnetic storm.

72
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,560
‐ Pulses have penetrated
the outer shields

73
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:03,645
and are compounding
the damage to the hull.

74
00:06:03,645 --> 00:06:04,980
We're on red alert.

75
00:06:09,526 --> 00:06:12,029
[alarm blaring]

76
00:06:17,534 --> 00:06:20,287
‐ This isn't a storm.
It's a test.

77
00:06:24,541 --> 00:06:26,835
‐ "Argonaut's" interior
has been compromised.

78
00:06:26,835 --> 00:06:29,171
MAN: At this rate,
we'll be torn apart!

79
00:06:29,171 --> 00:06:31,507
A field is growing
in our output!

80
00:06:31,507 --> 00:06:35,010
Total shield failure
in 11.6 minutes!

81
00:06:35,010 --> 00:06:38,430
‐ We have no choice
but to turn the ship around.

82
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:40,307
DHIANEILA: No, Captain.

83
00:06:40,307 --> 00:06:41,725
‐ Your Highness.
[beeps]

84
00:06:41,725 --> 00:06:43,727
‐ Receiving a transmission.

85
00:06:43,727 --> 00:06:46,647
Displaying the data now.

86
00:06:48,941 --> 00:06:52,694
MOBEEDO: That isn't a course.
What the hell is this?

87
00:06:52,694 --> 00:06:54,404
‐ Delphi has approved
the procedure

88
00:06:54,404 --> 00:06:56,031
to unlock the frame.

89
00:06:56,031 --> 00:06:59,576
‐ You can't seriously want us
to deploy the main cannon.

90
00:06:59,576 --> 00:07:01,078
That's insane!

91
00:07:01,078 --> 00:07:02,830
‐ That wasn't my order.

92
00:07:02,830 --> 00:07:05,499
Your Highness, just what
are you trying to do here?

93
00:07:05,499 --> 00:07:07,501
‐ This ordeal is meant
to test us.

94
00:07:07,501 --> 00:07:09,586
The Golden Tribe is trying
to find out if we are

95
00:07:09,586 --> 00:07:12,923
truly willing to persevere and
open the path on our own.

96
00:07:12,923 --> 00:07:16,510
‐ I can't promise you
this is going to end well.

97
00:07:16,510 --> 00:07:19,638
‐ Please, believe in me,
Captain.

98
00:07:21,473 --> 00:07:25,352
‐ I guess even a saint needs
a soldier to do the dirty work.

99
00:07:25,352 --> 00:07:28,480
Lucky for both us,
I don't mind.

100
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,565
Hmm.

101
00:07:29,565 --> 00:07:31,775
Maintain shields
at full power!

102
00:07:31,775 --> 00:07:32,943
Prepare to discharge

103
00:07:32,943 --> 00:07:34,361
the main cannon
of the "Argonaut"

104
00:07:34,361 --> 00:07:36,738
at the coordinates
provided by the princess!

105
00:07:36,738 --> 00:07:38,490
‐ But Captain,
you're asking us

106
00:07:38,490 --> 00:07:40,200
to pump more energy
into the shields

107
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:42,452
while we're still powering up
the main cannon.

108
00:07:42,452 --> 00:07:44,621
It can't be done
under these conditions.

109
00:07:44,621 --> 00:07:46,290
‐ If we don't turn around
right now,

110
00:07:46,290 --> 00:07:48,292
there's no way the "Argonaut"
will survive this.

111
00:07:48,292 --> 00:07:50,794
‐ The princess has never
steered us wrong before,

112
00:07:50,794 --> 00:07:52,963
and you'll take
her orders now!

113
00:07:56,383 --> 00:07:59,094
There's a lot more at stake here
than our own lives,

114
00:07:59,094 --> 00:08:00,345
ladies and gentlemen.

115
00:08:00,345 --> 00:08:03,265
It's the future
of our entire species.

116
00:08:03,265 --> 00:08:07,853
Now more than ever,
we have to give it our all.

117
00:08:11,481 --> 00:08:13,567
‐ Reconfiguring
shield coverage.

118
00:08:13,567 --> 00:08:15,027
Now unlocking the hull.

119
00:08:15,027 --> 00:08:19,489
[all talking at once]

120
00:08:19,489 --> 00:08:21,325
‐ Now they need
active simulations

121
00:08:21,325 --> 00:08:23,327
to determine
any possible errors.

122
00:08:23,327 --> 00:08:25,621
‐ Deploy all
available Organ units!

123
00:08:25,621 --> 00:08:28,916
Position them where the hull
is most vulnerable!

124
00:08:28,916 --> 00:08:33,211
Now we'll see whether we pass
this test, or fail it.

125
00:08:39,009 --> 00:08:40,344
WOMAN: Begin [indistinct]
the outer hull.

126
00:08:40,344 --> 00:08:42,429
MAN: Starboard lock
is disengaged.

127
00:08:42,429 --> 00:08:44,598
Beginning first stage
of deployment.

128
00:08:49,895 --> 00:08:52,231
WOMAN: Confirming release
of the outer hull lock.

129
00:08:52,231 --> 00:08:54,358
Moving on to stage two.

130
00:08:54,358 --> 00:08:56,318
MAN: Releasing the middle axis.

131
00:08:56,318 --> 00:08:58,862
The outer hull and sail
are now fully open.

132
00:08:58,862 --> 00:09:00,447
‐ Attention, all units.

133
00:09:00,447 --> 00:09:02,449
Be prepared to engage
your shields.

134
00:09:12,209 --> 00:09:15,087
‐ Stop it!
Don't you break now!

135
00:09:15,087 --> 00:09:16,255
[groaning]

136
00:09:16,255 --> 00:09:19,675
This'll never work!
Never!

137
00:09:19,675 --> 00:09:23,178
MAN: [indistinct].
Muzzle is now exposed.

138
00:09:28,475 --> 00:09:29,893
WOMAN:
All locks have been checked.

139
00:09:29,893 --> 00:09:32,020
The outer hull is in place.

140
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:35,232
Communication system is
off‐line.

141
00:09:35,232 --> 00:09:38,402
[all talking at once]

142
00:09:38,402 --> 00:09:40,070
‐ Main cannon
has been deployed.

143
00:09:40,070 --> 00:09:41,947
The margin of error
for target alignment

144
00:09:41,947 --> 00:09:43,198
is approaching zero.

145
00:09:43,198 --> 00:09:44,908
‐ Problem in propulsion room A.

146
00:09:44,908 --> 00:09:46,535
It looks like we're losing
the thruster.

147
00:09:46,535 --> 00:09:49,705
‐ We can only maintain firing
position for 60 seconds,

148
00:09:49,705 --> 00:09:50,914
so hurry up and aim!

149
00:09:50,914 --> 00:09:52,374
WOMAN:
Connecting the firing circuits.

150
00:09:52,374 --> 00:09:55,085
Activating all accelerators.

151
00:09:55,085 --> 00:09:57,087
‐ It's getting even worse
out there.

152
00:09:57,087 --> 00:10:00,090
We've got to try and concentrate
more energy on Dhianeila.

153
00:10:00,090 --> 00:10:03,135
No matter what happens, we can't
let her become too weak.

154
00:10:03,135 --> 00:10:04,886
All of us here
would give our lives

155
00:10:04,886 --> 00:10:08,515
to support you in your quest.
That is our mission

156
00:10:08,515 --> 00:10:11,601
and my personal oath
to you, Dhianeila.

157
00:10:11,601 --> 00:10:14,313
MAN: Target is locked on.
Awaiting authorization.

158
00:10:15,689 --> 00:10:18,317
WOMAN: Biological [indistinct]
has been entered.

159
00:10:18,317 --> 00:10:20,902
Approving the final code
of star blaster.

160
00:10:20,902 --> 00:10:22,154
MAN: Energy level is rising.

161
00:10:22,154 --> 00:10:24,323
50 seconds
until launch criticality.

162
00:10:26,116 --> 00:10:29,119
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

163
00:10:29,119 --> 00:10:34,875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

164
00:10:34,875 --> 00:10:37,669
All accelerators are
functioning normally.

165
00:10:37,669 --> 00:10:39,755
Ten seconds
until criticality.

166
00:10:39,755 --> 00:10:44,760
Nine, eight, seven,
six, five,

167
00:10:44,760 --> 00:10:49,306
four, three, two,
one, zero.

168
00:10:49,306 --> 00:10:51,892
WOMAN: Main cannon is ready
to launch.

169
00:10:52,934 --> 00:10:54,186
‐ Fire.

170
00:11:07,949 --> 00:11:10,994
<i>[ethereal music]</i>

171
00:11:10,994 --> 00:11:15,874
<i>♪ ♪</i>

172
00:11:19,252 --> 00:11:21,213
‐ The main cannon was aimed
and fired.

173
00:11:21,213 --> 00:11:22,672
The status
of our inertial control

174
00:11:22,672 --> 00:11:24,257
and shield systems
is unknown.

175
00:11:24,257 --> 00:11:26,051
‐ The fore thruster
is damaged.

176
00:11:26,051 --> 00:11:27,511
We're losing pressure fast!

177
00:11:27,511 --> 00:11:29,137
‐ We can try to recover
navigation

178
00:11:29,137 --> 00:11:30,514
on the backup circuit.

179
00:11:34,059 --> 00:11:35,644
‐ What's this?

180
00:11:35,644 --> 00:11:38,188
‐ Conditions outside the ship
are now favorable, Master.

181
00:11:38,188 --> 00:11:41,191
We're back on the scheduled
course with no margin of error.

182
00:11:41,191 --> 00:11:42,859
‐ What the hell is going on?

183
00:11:42,859 --> 00:11:44,861
How can the ship
still be moving?

184
00:11:44,861 --> 00:11:47,239
‐ The unknown field is
changing rapidly.

185
00:11:47,239 --> 00:11:51,535
It's amazing. It appears
to have become pure gravity.

186
00:11:51,535 --> 00:11:54,204
‐ Like a path of stars.

187
00:11:55,122 --> 00:11:58,166
‐ A Starway has been born.

188
00:11:58,166 --> 00:12:01,211
<i>[peaceful music]</i>

189
00:12:01,211 --> 00:12:05,257
<i>♪ ♪</i>

190
00:12:05,257 --> 00:12:06,800
‐ [sighs]

191
00:12:12,264 --> 00:12:14,307
‐ Elysium.

192
00:12:16,101 --> 00:12:20,063
‐ We're here,
home world of the Golden Tribe.

193
00:12:20,063 --> 00:12:21,314
‐ Wow.

194
00:12:27,821 --> 00:12:31,032
‐ The shield. Captain,
is the Silver Tribe here?

195
00:12:31,032 --> 00:12:33,118
‐ I doubt they've arrived yet.

196
00:12:33,118 --> 00:12:35,829
Those are the shields that were
given to the Silver Tribe.

197
00:12:35,829 --> 00:12:38,832
I suspect those are
the original.

198
00:12:43,587 --> 00:12:45,755
DHIANEILA:
The planet is welcoming us.

199
00:12:45,755 --> 00:12:48,925
Captain, please be prepared
to make your descent.

200
00:12:48,925 --> 00:12:50,802
‐ Your Highness‐‐

201
00:12:50,802 --> 00:12:52,929
Of course you'll go down there
on your own

202
00:12:52,929 --> 00:12:55,974
no matter what I say.
Just a moment.

203
00:12:55,974 --> 00:12:59,436
Allow me to restructure
the Organ unit for you.

204
00:12:59,436 --> 00:13:01,938
‐ Thank you so very much,
Captain.

205
00:13:01,938 --> 00:13:03,732
‐ We're so proud of you.

206
00:13:03,732 --> 00:13:05,066
‐ And thank you.

207
00:13:05,066 --> 00:13:06,568
I never could've found
the path,

208
00:13:06,568 --> 00:13:08,695
or made here alive
for that matter,

209
00:13:08,695 --> 00:13:11,490
if it wasn't
for your loyal service.

210
00:13:14,159 --> 00:13:16,244
‐ Your Highness,
will you allow me

211
00:13:16,244 --> 00:13:19,039
to stay be your side
until the very end?

212
00:13:19,039 --> 00:13:20,332
‐ Of course.

213
00:13:23,168 --> 00:13:25,420
‐ Operation efficiency
is down by half.

214
00:13:25,420 --> 00:13:27,631
There's no timetable
for navigation repairs.

215
00:13:27,631 --> 00:13:29,716
‐ Due to the shortage
of supplies, over half

216
00:13:29,716 --> 00:13:32,969
of the 247 damaged blocks
cannot be repaired.

217
00:13:32,969 --> 00:13:35,805
‐ Our defensive capabilities
have been compromised,

218
00:13:35,805 --> 00:13:37,224
and due to energy consumption,

219
00:13:37,224 --> 00:13:40,060
so has our ability
to mount a counterattack.

220
00:13:40,060 --> 00:13:43,605
‐ Not bad, considering that
storm should have destroyed us.

221
00:13:43,605 --> 00:13:45,357
But it didn't,
and I would like to thank

222
00:13:45,357 --> 00:13:48,777
each and every one of you
for being at your best.

223
00:13:48,777 --> 00:13:50,862
‐ Should we send out
a distress signal, sir?

224
00:13:50,862 --> 00:13:53,907
‐ I don't believe this is
a ghost ship just yet.

225
00:13:53,907 --> 00:13:56,409
Besides, it might attract
the enemy.

226
00:13:56,409 --> 00:13:58,787
We'll use it if there's
no other option.

227
00:13:58,787 --> 00:14:01,998
Start the repairs on all
our navigational components.

228
00:14:01,998 --> 00:14:04,501
‐ The shuttle unit Basilis
is now prepared

229
00:14:04,501 --> 00:14:06,002
for its descent, master.

230
00:14:06,002 --> 00:14:08,463
‐ At long last our princess
shall set foot

231
00:14:08,463 --> 00:14:10,632
on the Golden Tribe's
mother planet.

232
00:14:10,632 --> 00:14:13,510
Send every available Organ unit
for her protection.

233
00:14:13,510 --> 00:14:15,178
WOMAN: The course is set.
Open the bay.

234
00:14:15,178 --> 00:14:16,763
WOMAN: Ready to move out.

235
00:14:21,935 --> 00:14:23,645
‐ We don't know how
the Hedron shield

236
00:14:23,645 --> 00:14:26,690
surrounding the planet will
react, so stay on alert.

237
00:14:26,690 --> 00:14:28,525
Anything could happen
out there.

238
00:14:28,525 --> 00:14:29,567
‐ Roger that.

239
00:14:29,567 --> 00:14:31,361
WOMAN:
We have engine ignition.

240
00:14:31,361 --> 00:14:33,363
Moving out.

241
00:14:39,452 --> 00:14:42,539
<i>[inspiring music]</i>

242
00:14:42,539 --> 00:14:49,546
<i>♪ ♪</i>

243
00:15:09,774 --> 00:15:12,861
[balls shimmering]

244
00:15:53,568 --> 00:15:56,321
‐ All descending units,
change course now.

245
00:16:19,803 --> 00:16:21,054
The atmosphere changed

246
00:16:21,054 --> 00:16:22,931
to accommodate
our presence here.

247
00:16:22,931 --> 00:16:26,643
Those are the optimum conditions
for humans to survive.

248
00:16:26,643 --> 00:16:27,894
‐ It's time.

249
00:16:27,894 --> 00:16:30,438
We won't need to wear a suit.

250
00:16:30,438 --> 00:16:33,024
Let us accept
this planet's welcome.

251
00:16:36,820 --> 00:16:38,530
Everyone wait here.

252
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:39,864
‐ Dhianeila, please.

253
00:16:39,864 --> 00:16:41,157
‐ At least take us with you.

254
00:16:41,157 --> 00:16:42,659
‐ It could be dangerous.

255
00:16:42,659 --> 00:16:44,661
‐ There's no need for you
to be concerned.

256
00:16:44,661 --> 00:16:46,204
I just want to feel
the thoughts

257
00:16:46,204 --> 00:16:49,040
that have been left
on this planet.

258
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:51,709
‐ I'd feel better
about this

259
00:16:51,709 --> 00:16:53,920
if the princess had
an escort down there.

260
00:16:55,171 --> 00:16:56,506
‐ Let's keep our eyes open.

261
00:16:56,506 --> 00:16:59,008
We don't want to overlook
anything.

262
00:17:07,267 --> 00:17:09,352
[energy ringing]

263
00:17:09,352 --> 00:17:11,646
‐ Such powerful thoughts.

264
00:17:11,646 --> 00:17:14,149
But now you are nowhere
to be found on this planet

265
00:17:14,149 --> 00:17:16,151
or this universe.

266
00:17:16,151 --> 00:17:18,319
Why did you leave?

267
00:17:23,199 --> 00:17:26,244
[surging energy]

268
00:17:27,287 --> 00:17:29,205
To fill...

269
00:17:29,205 --> 00:17:31,708
all of existence...

270
00:17:31,708 --> 00:17:34,753
with Starways.

271
00:17:39,257 --> 00:17:40,675
ROM: That is a lie.

272
00:17:40,675 --> 00:17:43,720
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

273
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:44,721
<i>♪ ♪</i>

274
00:17:44,721 --> 00:17:46,055
[alarm blaring]

275
00:17:46,055 --> 00:17:48,016
‐ Of course,
they followed us.

276
00:17:48,016 --> 00:17:51,060
WOMAN: Incoming enemy ship,
vector 1.98.

277
00:17:51,060 --> 00:17:54,522
MAN: We have no effective
counter attack available to us.

278
00:17:54,522 --> 00:17:57,734
MOBEEDO: All Organ units proceed
to the surface at once.

279
00:17:57,734 --> 00:18:00,487
Maintain shields
at maximum capacity.

280
00:18:00,487 --> 00:18:02,280
We've got to protect her!

281
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:04,365
Plot a collision course
immediately!

282
00:18:04,365 --> 00:18:06,868
‐ Dhianeila!

283
00:18:06,868 --> 00:18:09,871
‐ Before any blood is spilled,
please meditate with me.

284
00:18:09,871 --> 00:18:12,165
Try to feel
the immense wealth of thoughts

285
00:18:12,165 --> 00:18:14,209
that were left here for us.

286
00:18:14,209 --> 00:18:17,837
‐ Long before you
and your vile kind arrived

287
00:18:17,837 --> 00:18:19,923
I scoured Elysium
for anything

288
00:18:19,923 --> 00:18:22,592
the Golden Tribe may have
left behind,

289
00:18:22,592 --> 00:18:24,552
but I discovered nothing.

290
00:18:24,552 --> 00:18:27,555
They feared their great power
would be taken from them,

291
00:18:27,555 --> 00:18:31,392
so they abandoned this universe.
They they abandoned us.

292
00:18:31,392 --> 00:18:32,685
‐ You're wrong.

293
00:18:32,685 --> 00:18:34,562
We simply weren't prepared
to inherit

294
00:18:34,562 --> 00:18:36,481
a power of that magnitude.

295
00:18:38,274 --> 00:18:40,944
‐ The Nodos are all
they left for us.

296
00:18:40,944 --> 00:18:43,279
The power to destroy it all.

297
00:18:43,279 --> 00:18:46,491
That was the true intention
of the Golden Tribe.

298
00:18:47,534 --> 00:18:49,869
‐ I don't care anymore.

299
00:18:49,869 --> 00:18:50,995
[sobs]

300
00:18:50,995 --> 00:18:54,624
Kervius,
erase this suffering.

301
00:18:54,624 --> 00:18:57,168
Erase me.

302
00:18:58,670 --> 00:19:00,547
‐ Don't you see?
They knew we would find

303
00:19:00,547 --> 00:19:02,757
the location
of their home planet.

304
00:19:02,757 --> 00:19:05,051
‐ Hmm.
That may be true.

305
00:19:05,051 --> 00:19:07,303
The Golden Tribe,
in their infinite wisdom,

306
00:19:07,303 --> 00:19:09,222
may have foreseen this,
and there is

307
00:19:09,222 --> 00:19:12,934
only one possible reason
I could have been brought here.

308
00:19:12,934 --> 00:19:15,270
‐ No, don't!

309
00:19:15,270 --> 00:19:19,065
ROM: To erase all that has been
tainted by the Golden Tribe.

310
00:19:20,859 --> 00:19:22,443
‐ Kervius.

311
00:19:23,820 --> 00:19:26,364
‐ Keep energy on the shield
at the point of contact!

312
00:19:26,364 --> 00:19:27,699
Fight back!

313
00:19:27,699 --> 00:19:30,785
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

314
00:19:30,785 --> 00:19:37,792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

315
00:19:47,427 --> 00:19:49,220
It protected us.

316
00:19:49,220 --> 00:19:52,098
‐ All systems are failing.
We're going to crash!

317
00:19:52,098 --> 00:19:53,474
‐ Expand the ship's body

318
00:19:53,474 --> 00:19:55,101
as soon as we hit
the atmosphere.

319
00:19:55,101 --> 00:19:57,729
We've got to diffuse
the shock of the fall.

320
00:20:03,985 --> 00:20:05,320
‐ Come, kill.

321
00:20:05,320 --> 00:20:08,489
With this you conclude
your Labors, Yuty.

322
00:20:17,081 --> 00:20:18,499
‐ Frenzy.

323
00:20:18,499 --> 00:20:21,502
Is that the true intention
of the Golden Tribe?

324
00:20:21,502 --> 00:20:23,546
Does this mean that our future
is destined

325
00:20:23,546 --> 00:20:26,883
to be forged
from chaos and despair?

326
00:20:26,883 --> 00:20:28,176
‐ Dhianeila.

327
00:20:29,385 --> 00:20:30,803
The "Argonaut."

328
00:20:30,803 --> 00:20:34,474
‐ By the gods.
It's going down.

329
00:20:36,726 --> 00:20:39,228
‐ All remaining thrusters have
been rendered inoperative.

330
00:20:39,228 --> 00:20:41,230
‐ Focus all the shields
under the ship!

331
00:20:41,230 --> 00:20:43,107
Maintain the peak angle
of approach,

332
00:20:43,107 --> 00:20:45,234
otherwise the ship will
snap in half!

333
00:20:45,234 --> 00:20:46,861
‐ Impact is imminent, Captain.

334
00:20:46,861 --> 00:20:49,739
‐ Release every insulating wall
on the "Argonaut"!

335
00:20:49,739 --> 00:20:51,699
Spread impact of reentry!

336
00:20:51,699 --> 00:20:54,327
We're not done for just yet!

337
00:21:20,019 --> 00:21:23,064
[groaning]

338
00:21:24,857 --> 00:21:26,693
[grunts]

339
00:21:26,693 --> 00:21:28,736
Bee, report.

340
00:21:32,448 --> 00:21:35,785
You've done a fine job, Bee.

341
00:21:37,453 --> 00:21:39,539
‐ What happened?

342
00:21:39,539 --> 00:21:43,126
The Silver Tribe!
You did this to him!

343
00:21:43,126 --> 00:21:46,129
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

344
00:21:46,129 --> 00:21:49,924
<i>♪ ♪</i>

345
00:21:49,924 --> 00:21:51,175
Damn it.

346
00:21:52,885 --> 00:21:55,722
‐ Even if he destroys
each one of us,

347
00:21:55,722 --> 00:21:58,099
the path to the future
will go on.

348
00:22:01,477 --> 00:22:03,771
Our hope will never die.

349
00:22:05,940 --> 00:22:07,233
‐ Let's go.

350
00:22:11,070 --> 00:22:12,363
‐ [grumbles]

351
00:22:19,454 --> 00:22:21,039
‐ [grunting]

352
00:22:34,010 --> 00:22:37,847
‐ [roars]

353
00:22:37,847 --> 00:22:40,850
<i>["Azurite" by Tae Urakabe]</i>

354
00:22:40,850 --> 00:22:43,978
<i>[woman singing in Japanese]</i>

355
00:22:43,978 --> 00:22:50,985
<i>♪ ♪</i>

356
00:23:48,417 --> 00:23:51,921
DHIANEILA: We embrace
possibilities and hope.

357
00:23:51,921 --> 00:23:56,592
Next time on "Heroic Age,"
episode 15, "The Final Labor."

